' PlantUML example — Technology layer: physical/execution deployment of the
' EU portfolio applications.
'
' Derived from:
'   - canon/views/applications/eu-portfolio.applications.transitrix.yaml
'       APPLICATION-OMS-1: vendor "Internal" -> self-hosted node.
'       APPLICATION-CRM-1: vendor "Salesforce" -> external SaaS cloud node.
'   - canon/elements/04_technology/equipment/EQUIPMENT-SCANNER-1.yaml
'       "Handheld barcode scanner used in the warehouse."
'
' Not a duplicate of canon/views/c4infrastructure/network-zones.md: that
' Mermaid flowchart shows network *zones* and traffic crossing them. This
' UML deployment diagram shows formal deployment semantics instead — nodes,
' artifacts, and execution environments — detail the flowchart form doesn't
' carry (e.g. what artifact runs where, not just which zone talks to which).

!include transitrix-theme.puml
@startuml EU portfolio — deployment

node "Customer browser" as Browser #e8f2f5

node "Acme Corp datacenter (Internal)" as DC #f4f9fb {
  node "App server" as AppSrv #e8f2f5 {
    artifact "APPLICATION-OMS-1" as OMS #ccd8dc
  }
  database "Active-order DB" as DB #e8f2f5
}

cloud "Salesforce Cloud (SaaS)" as SFCloud #f4f9fb {
  node "Salesforce platform" as SFNode #e8f2f5 {
    artifact "APPLICATION-CRM-1" as CRM #ccd8dc
  }
}

node "Warehouse LAN (on-premise)" as WH #f4f9fb {
  artifact "EQUIPMENT-SCANNER-1\n(Barcode scanner)" as Scanner #e8f2f5
}

Browser --> AppSrv : HTTPS
AppSrv --> DB : reads/writes
AppSrv --> SFNode : REST outbound (order & erasure events)
Scanner --> AppSrv : scan events (pick & pack)

@enduml
